Power of Fire - SolB - I can do myself if I would just do it<br>
Power of Water - Kaesora - I think I can do myself<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
ok, power of fire, drops off blazing elementals and lava elementals.  I could only get it to drop from the blazing ones, in the blazing elemental pit-trap thingy in the northern part of SolA.  you'll see what I mean if you look at the eqAtlas.com map.  Not a common drop, so get rdy to nestle in and sit.  I did this around lvl 40-42...so you should have absolutely no trouble.  If you want company, just ask.<br>
<br>
power of water.  every single time i go to help someone kill Xalgoz, we accidentally get one to drop.  I was holding one to MQ for you for a long-ass time...but i had to destroy it.  not tough to replace.  again, something you can easily do solo.  if you look at the map of kaesora, the room south of the entrance with the broken floor revealing a tunnel betwork beneath (you have to go this way to get to Xalgoz) there are spermy-guys in that area.  between there and the library were the most common places for the raveners.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Torch of the Elements - Neh Ashiir in CoM - Need raid<br>
Burning Embers - Burning Woods - 1 group?<br>
Blazing Wand - not sure<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Torch.  yeah, when Neh'Ashiir doesn't drop the ORS, its usually the torch instead.  tough tradeoff.<br>
<br>
burning embers from Nezekezena.  Depends on the group.  we used to hunt her back when the ave lvl in the guild was around 53.  two groups she was a tough cookie.  now, we dominated her last time we met.  you will need a healer of some sort, she DOES gate/summon.  Since she drops a bard epic piece, bards are easily convinced they should help you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   unfortunately for magi, the bard drop is common, the mage drop is (of course) rare.<br>
<br>
blazing wand.  Undertow in Kedge.  get your swim trunks on.  he is in the temple in the northern part of the zone (read as pain in the ass).  generally, you go for either phinny or him (whoever is up) then evac/gate/get the hell out and go back in to make a trip to the other mob.  he is about as common as phinny or even less.  honestly, i have killed phinny more times than i have seen undertow up.  not promising.  he is basically a mini-phinny spell and power wise.  is a seahorse wizzy.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Tears of Erolisi - 1 group?<br>
Rain of Karana <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Tears from Captain Rottgrime in the outpost.  I gathered a massive overkill crowd for this since pulling NPC's out of the outpost is not a common thing.  Turns out this guy is a bit of a wimp with a tank or multi-earth pets in his face.  THE big problem is pulling him, without adds.  the best way to do this is to have a monk pull him, then have someone (like dear old pens with his lovely faction) hail him to hold him outside the outpost.  Serano was on harmony duty to keep the golems from getting antsy.  Quite the golem entertainer i must say <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
rain of karana.  Tarbul Earthstrider.  Took him down with some help from one other druid (who died in the process) when i was no higher than lvl 40, which is a bit low to tackle this guy, but I did it anyhow.  you should be able to own him up with maybe one other person if not yourself.  I haven't seen him since the day I killed him, so not sure what he cons, and forget how hard he hit for.<br>
<br>
Nistari, did you say you have already assembled the Power of the Elements?  I remembered you still needed pages from guk and such, just wonderin.<br>
